# Cursor Rules for School Management System

## Project Context
This is a school management system with:
- Backend: Python FastAPI (simplified_api.py) 
- Frontend: Vanilla JavaScript modules
- Database: PostgreSQL via production API

## Code Style Guidelines
- Use ES6+ JavaScript features
- Avoid TypeScript validation and suggestions
- Keep vanilla JavaScript without frameworks
- Use modular approach with ES6 imports/exports

## Editor Behavior
- Disable automatic type checking
- Disable JavaScript/TypeScript suggestions
- Disable auto-imports from package.json
- Focus on vanilla JavaScript without IntelliSense interference

## File Handling
- Main JavaScript files are in js/modules/
- Python files are in backend/
- Ignore __pycache__ and .pyc files
- HTML files use script type="module"

## Development Notes
- API runs at https://apinazarerodrigues.86dynamics.com.br/api
- Database uses PostgreSQL with explicit type casting (::numeric)
- Frontend handles bulletin generation and student grade management 